{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "ipbuilding-gateway-v1",
    "name": "IPBuilding Gateway",
    "description": "Northbound REST API for the IPBuilding open field-bus gateway.\n\n## Base URL\n{{base_url}}\n\n## Entity ID format\nAll device identifiers use the format `{module_ip}-{channel}` (e.g. `10.10.1.30-0`) or a custom slug (e.g. `keuken-led`).  The device type (relay/dimmer) is resolved server-side from `devices.json` and is never part of the client-supplied ID — this prevents type-spoofing.\n\n## Device types\n- **Relay** — supports actions: `ON`, `OFF`, `PULSE`\n- **Dimmer** — supports action: `DIM` with integer `value` 0–100\n\n## Responses\n- `GET /api/v1/devices` returns `{\"devices\": [...]}`\n- Command POST returns `{\"ok\": true}` on success, `{\"ok\": false, \"error\": \"...\"}` on failure\n- Unknown entity_id → HTTP 404\n- Missing action → HTTP 400\n- Unsupported action → HTTP 422\n\n## WebSocket\nWebSocket endpoint at `/ws` for real-time `state_changed` and `button_event` messages — see `docs/api/websocket.md`.  WebSocket requests are not included in this collection (Postman/PAW export limitation).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Modules",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List modules",
          "event": [],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/modules",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "modules"]
            },
            "description": "Return all physical field-bus modules with firmware, MAC, and cached network metadata.\n\n**Response 200:** `{\"modules\": [{\"id\": \"00:24:77:52:ac:be\", \"ip\": \"10.10.1.30\", ...}]}`"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get module",
          "event": [],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/modules/{{module_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "modules", "{{module_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Return a single module by its MAC-based module_id.\n\n**Response 200:** single module object.\n\n**Response 404:** `{\"error\": \"not found\"}`"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh modules",
          "event": [],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}
            ],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{}"},
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/modules/refresh",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "modules", "refresh"]
            },
            "description": "Re-fetch getSysSet and getButtons from all field modules. Updates in-memory metadata cache.\n\n**Response 200:** `{\"modules\": [...]}`"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
